732818f-b.title: Recreation and hobbies - Bird raising.
732818f-b.text:
(1)
Breeding pigeons is a common place hobby amongst New Yorkers. Both young and old utilise the roofs and housetops for the purpose. The one shown is at Catherine near Cherry Streets.
March 6, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
Another breeders flock atop the Underhill Building at 37th Street
east of 10th Ave.
May 23, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same as No. 1.
March 6, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
